TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;
$showPartialCredit = 0;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 


Let \[p(x) = x^3-3x^2-2x+1.\]

$BR
\(p(-2)\) can be computed via synthetic division by
filling in for the letters \(a\) through \(g\) in the table

\[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 & -3 & -2 & 1 \\
  & b & d & f \\
a & c & e & g \\
\end{array}
\]

where


$BR  \{ ans_rule(5) \} \(=a\),
EOT
ANS(num_cmp( 1));


TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
$BR  \{ ans_rule(5) \} \(=b\),
EOT
ANS(num_cmp( -2));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
$BR  \{ ans_rule(5) \} \(=c\),
EOT
ANS(num_cmp( -5));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
$BR  \{ ans_rule(5) \} \(=d\),
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(10));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
$BR  \{ ans_rule(5) \} \(=e\),
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(8));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
$BR  \{ ans_rule(5) \} \(=f\),
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(-16));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
$BR  \{ ans_rule(5) \} \(=g\).
$BR
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(-15));


TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
Moreover,
\(p(-2) =\) \{ ans_rule(5) \} and
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(-15));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
\(p(x)\) can be written as
\[p(x) = (x+2)q(x) + r \]
where 
$BR
\(q(x) =\) \{ ans_rule(20) \} is a quadratic polynomial and
EOT
ANS(fun_cmp("x*x-5*x+8", limits=>[[1,2]], vars=>["x"]));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
$BR
\(r=\)  \{ ans_rule(20) \} is a real number.
EOT


ANS(num_cmp(-15));


SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT')); 
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD Our matrix becomes

\[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 & -3 & -2 & 1 \\
  & -2 & 10 & -16 \\
1 & -5 & 8 & -15 \\
\end{array}
\]

Thus \[p(x) = (x+2)(x^2-5x+8) -15\]
and \(p(2) = -15\).
EOT



